{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566667","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566667"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18864"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18864"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.18,0.06,0.65,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11597"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100854"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11597","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11597"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18864"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83273"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"5738"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11320"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27299"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27305"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34084"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34248"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36819"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100854","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/100854"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA doctor has provided care for a child with severe mental health conditions for eight years. The doctor developed a strong therapeutic relationship with both the child and their parent during this time, providing significant emotional support. One month after the child transitions to adult healthcare services at age 16, the parent contacts the doctor suggesting they meet socially.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate professional response from the doctor?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Accept the invitation since the therapeutic relationship has ended","Ensure the parent is seeing another General Practitioner then consider the relationship","Wait six months before accepting the invitation","Decline the invitation","Maintain social media contact only"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edecline the invitation\u003C/strong\u003E. This case involves significant risk factors identified by the Medical Board, including long-term emotional/psychological treatment, high degree of emotional dependence, and the parent\u0027s close involvement in critical care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccept the invitation since the therapeutic relationship has ended\u003C/strong\u003E - The power imbalance and emotional dynamics persist beyond the formal end of care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnsure the parent is seeing another General Practitioner then consider the relationship\u003C/strong\u003E - The previous therapeutic relationship creates an ongoing ethical barrier regardless of current care arrangements\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait six months before accepting the invitation\u003C/strong\u003E - No time period makes this appropriate given the long-term psychological care and emotional dependency\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaintain social media contact only\u003C/strong\u003E - Any form of personal relationship would be inappropriate given the complex dynamics and potential for exploitation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe length of care, psychological nature of treatment, and emotional involvement of the parent make any personal relationship inappropriate and potentially exploitative, even after formal care has ended. This aspect of professionalism must be maintained, no matter what the environment. Certainly in a small rural community the parent and the doctor might meet each other whilst shopping or at social events and in such circumstances the doctor can be friendly, polite and professional while maintaining boundaries.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Professional boundaries must be maintained with patients and their close family members, especially in cases of long-term psychological care.","The power imbalance and emotional dependency created during long-term care of vulnerable patients extends to their family members.","Sexual or romantic relationships with parents of patients are inappropriate due to the risk of exploitation and complex emotional dynamics."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","AHPRA and National Boards. Sexual boundaries in the doctor-patient relationship [internet]. 2020 [CIted 2025 Jan 16]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/sexual-boundaries-guidelines.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83273"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18864"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/83273"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-27T14:09:10+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-27T14:09:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11597"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"100854"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"78","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/78"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level III","synonyms":null,"description":"Apply, analyze, evaluate, and create (implementing, organizing, and critiquing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data"